<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,812]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,352,487,513]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Dr. James Wappes (
<collectionCode box="[974,1072,488,514]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">ACMT</collectionCode>
), in recognition of his great contribution to the knowledge of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[688,861,525,551]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
