<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,812]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,333,637,663]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Comments</emphasis>
. The pattern and coloration of 
<taxonomicName authority="Monne &amp; Monne" authorityName="Monne &amp; Monne" box="[707,1166,637,663]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Colobothea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wappesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[707,950,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Colobothea wappesi</emphasis>
Monné &amp; Monné
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1174,1269,637,663]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1174,1269,637,663]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Aurivillius, 1902" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1902" box="[257,604,674,700]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Colobothea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivis">
<emphasis box="[257,385,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">C. declivis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius" box="[394,604,674,700]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1902) Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 7. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 23, 207 - 224." type="journal article" year="1902">
Aurivillius, 
<number box="[541,604,674,700]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" value="1902.0">1902</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the yellow lateral stripe of the pronotum is not projected on the elytra, the humeri are sharply oblique, and the metasternum lacks patches of yellow pubescence. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1313,1436,712,737]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Colobothea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivis">
<emphasis box="[1313,1436,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">C. declivis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the yellow lateral stripe of the pronotum is projected posteriorly on the basal ¼ or 
<number box="[1110,1121,749,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1133,1148,749,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
of the elytra; the humeri are less oblique, and the metasternum has a more or less developed patch of yellow pubescence.
</paragraph>
